  "body": "[Deno](https://deno.land) is the next-gen version of nodejs, built specifically for TypeScript. Hardhat is a modern TypeScript project that could fit very well with deno.\r\n\r\nHere are some tools that can help:\r\n- [Denoify](https://github.com/garronej/denoify) is a library that can aid in supporting deno with minimal changes to Hardhat's codebase\r\n- [dpx](https://github.com/denorg/dpx) is analogous to node's npx, could it be used to execute the cli?\r\n- Some services attempt to provide deno support automatically (Skypack: https://cdn.skypack.dev/hardhat?dts JSPM: https://dev.jspm.io/hardhat) but don't seem to work out of the box\r\n- Ethers.js is also a modern Typescript repo that's often paired with Hardhat -- for reference, here's the corresponding deno issue: ethers-io/ethers.js#2009\r\n\r\nAre there any plans to support deno?",
