    "body": "Hey @sjmueller,\r\n\r\nWe don't have any plan to support Deno for now. The reason for this is that Hardhat is currently very tied to node and npm, both directly and through its dependencies. This will partially change in the future, as we are moving some parts of it to Rust.\r\n\r\nI'll close this for now, as it's not actionable. Feel free to open another issue in ~6 months.",
